.TH "DN-SCAN" "1" "2026-01-09" "" "DN-SCAN Manual"
.SH "NAME"
\*[self] \- scan to image and then transform the image
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "\*[self]"
[
.B "\-f"
.I "dir_path"
]
[
.B "\-b"
.I "base_name"
]
.YS
.SY "\*[self]"
.B "\-h"
.YS
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\*[self] uses
.I "scanimage"
to perform a scan. The user then has the opportunity to perform the following
operations on the resulting image: deskew (using ImageMagick), crop (using
shotwell), reduce file size/image resolutione (using ImageMagick).
.PP
The image is then saved to disk. The default directory path is "~/Downloads/"
but this can be changed with the
.I "-f"
option. The default filename is "image.png" but the file basename ran be
changed with the
.I "-b"
option. Note that filename collisions are avoided by adding a unique number to
the end of the basename.
.PP
Finally, the user is given an opportunity to request a pdf version of the final
image.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.BI "\-f  \-\-folder " "dir_path"
Destination directory for image file. Will be created if it does not exist.
Default: \(aq~/Downloads\(aq. Optional.
.TP
.BI "\-b  \-\-basename " "base_name"
Basename of image file to be created. Default: \(aqimage\(aq. Optional.
.TP
.B "\-v  \-\-verbose"
Print input lines as they are read (equivalent to \(aqset -o verbose\(aq).
Optional.
.TP
.B "\-d  \-\-debug"
Print input lines after command expansion (equivalent to \(aqset -o
xtrace\(aq). Optional.
.TP
.B "\-h  \-\-help"
Print help text and exit. Optional.
